                <head>156. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On September 4, the National Advisory Council on International Monetary and
                    Financial Problems met and discussed, as agenda item 2, the U.S. position on a
                    proposed increase in resources of the International Monetary Fund and the
                    International Bank for Reconstruction and Development. The minutes of this
                    portion of the meeting are printed as <ref target="#d35">Document 35</ref>.</p>
            </div>
